  "doc_id": "41967",
  "text": "The Gaussian background model-based detection algorithm was simple but not easy to be realized with HDL code. Genovese et al. [CITATION_1] implemented Gaussian mixture model (GMM) algorithm on Xilinx Virtex-6 FPGA with VHDL, which was capable of processing more than 45 fps in 1080p format. Genovese et al. [CITATION_2] implemented the OpenCV version of the GMM on Xilinx Virtex-6 FPGA and ASIC with VHDL, which was capable of processing 91 fps and 60 fps in 1080p, respectively. However, the studies mentioned above mainly aimed at processing capability of the circuits rather than the maintainability and user friendliness of the system.",
